://substack.com/redirect/ef0e0e8b-dc95-4f91-9a6f-e4c936a1a93b?j=3DeyJ1IjoiO=
XAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Ashlee Vance for Bloomberg
Cognition AI is full of sport-coders. Its staff has won a total of 10 gold =
medals at the top international competition [ https://substack.com/redirect=
/35a2b0a3-c2e5-4f3d-8b38-37ce1f81a5a8?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlN=
uaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], and Scott Wu says this background gives hi=
s startup an edge in the AI wars.
Humans rock, but AI is getting pretty great too.=20
On Tuesday, Cognition AI lit the internet on fire when they announced their=
 AI software engineer, Devin [ https://substack.com/redirect/7d9c24c3-cd9f-=
484b-a24a-22b6faf527d1?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqO=
sa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] (great name!). The tweet announcing the product currently =
has 27 million views.=20
I=E2=80=99ve gotten to play around with Devin over the last couple of days,=
 and it=E2=80=99s a totally different experience than you might be used to =
with something like ChatGPT. You tell Devin something you want to code =E2=
=80=94 a website, game, debugging your code, spinning up an LLM inside a Do=
cker container, whatever =E2=80=94 and it plans out the steps required, exe=
cutes them in order, and pings you when it needs something like an API key.=
=20
Given its name, I asked it to spin me up a site that has Devin and Maya=E2=
=80=99s names bouncing around the screen, which it did quickly and deployed=
 to Netlify [ https://substack.com/redirect/9e88a745-e51a-401d-9263-e6db380=
51066?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].
The early demo is impressive, especially when you consider that the company=
 officially incorporated two months ago, and it will only get smarter and f=
aster from here. The speed shouldn=E2=80=99t be surprising given that the t=
eam of 10 has won 10 IOI gold medals for competitive coding, and that its C=
EO, Scott Wu, did this when he was a kid:
If you=E2=80=99re a real diehard Not Boring reader, you may remember Scott=
=E2=80=99s brother, and Cognition AI team member, Neal Wu from the piece I =
